# Performance — Priority Order

**Firma:** HorosCode · **Produkt:** HorosCloud

## Priority Stack (Pass 1 Mockup→Code)

```
1. Design fidelity (98/100)     ← highest
2. Correctness (builds, binds)
3. Maintainability (reuse, tokens)
4. Performance optimization   ← lowest in Pass 1
```

**Never** sacrifice mockup fidelity for performance in Pass 1.

## When Performance Matters (Pass 2+)

After all regions approved and Shell assembled:

| Technique | When |
|-----------|------|
| `VirtualizingStackPanel` | Lists with 50+ items |
| Compiled bindings (`x:DataType`) | All new AXAML |
| Avoid deep visual trees | Profile shows layout cost |
| `WhenAnyValue` debounce | Search/filter ViewModels |
| Lazy-load heavy views | Tab panels not visible at start |

## Compiled Binding Example

```xml
<UserControl x:DataType="vm:DashboardViewModel"
             xmlns:vm="using:HorosCloud.Desktop.ViewModels">
  <TextBlock Text="{Binding Title}" />
  <!-- Compile-time binding check -->
</UserControl>
```

## Virtualization Example

```xml
<ListBox ItemsSource="{Binding Items}">
  <ListBox.ItemsPanel>
    <ItemsPanelTemplate>
      <VirtualizingStackPanel />
    </ItemsPanelTemplate>
  </ListBox.ItemsPanel>
</ListBox>
```

## Never in Pass 1

- **Never** skip mockup-accurate layout for "better performance"
- **Never** remove visual elements to reduce tree depth
- **Never** premature-optimize bindings before review passes
- **Never** delay Preview/Review for micro-optimizations

